WhatsOnstage Award, London – for Best Actress in a musical ‘Hello Again’
The term violent true believer was coined by forensic psychiatrist Dr. J. Reid Meloy, who has described several categories of such individuals and their motivation. The traits and possible disorders of VTBs are described in diagnostic systems DSM-IV and ICD-10 F, but VTB is not a medical diagnosis in itself — the term is used in the fields of forensic psychology and criminology. The typology is taught at the FBI Academy and is currently undergoing further validity research.
After the first season was concluded, Eyal Shani became famous, due to his eccentric treatment of food as poetry in the show, though Haim Cohen was the most famous of the judges, Shani became the symbol of the show and became a cultural icon in Israel.
